# Fluff Date: 2026-03-13 20:44:32
<overview>
<p>The Angerona Scout Suit is a medium-class battle armor design produced by StarCorps Industries on Terra for the Republic of the Sphere's Armed Forces. Entering service in 3083, the suit was purpose-built as a stealthy ground scout, offering its operators the ability to remain concealed while on the move. The Angerona earned a strong reputation among frontline formations for its effectiveness in forward reconnaissance operations deep in hostile territory, and it quickly became one of the Republic's most requested battle armor platforms.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Angerona pairs Improved Stealth Armor with a full camouflage system, allowing troopers to move at speed while remaining nearly invisible to most sensors. This combination addressed the primary shortcoming of earlier mimetic designs, which demanded complete immobility for effective concealment. Despite a medium weight class, overall armor protection skews lighter to keep the suit's profile consistent with its scouting role.</p><p>A Light Recoilless Rifle mounted in the right arm provides the primary offensive punch, comparable in damage output to a Magshot but at reduced range. An Anti-Personnel Weapon Mount on the left arm rounds out the loadout. Basic manipulators allow the suit to ride BattleMechs and vehicles, though the rifle's casing wraps around the right hand for stability, requiring it to be unlimbered before mounting another unit. The Angerona's ground speed of over thirty kilometers per hour comes at the cost of all jump capability, a deliberate trade-off that keeps the suit's acoustic and thermal signature low.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>Republic Armed Forces organized their Angerona troopers into standard four-trooper squads, consistent with Inner Sphere infantry doctrine. The VIII Hastati Sentinels received the first production suits for operational evaluation, with subsequent deliveries reaching other active line formations. Squads typically operated in pairs during scouting missions, providing mutual overwatch while one element advanced through contested terrain.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Republic Armed Forces identified a critical capability gap following the Jihad: the need for a mobile infantry scout that could remain undetected while traversing open terrain. Existing stealth technology imposed significant constraints on trooper mobility, limiting its utility for active reconnaissance. Drawing on lessons from Stone's Coalition campaign, RAF planners sought a suit that could hide and move at the same time.</p><p>StarCorps Industries, fresh off the success of the Kopis, accepted the contract at their Terra facility. The design team drew heavily from the Capellan Trinity concept, prioritizing sustained ground mobility over jump capability and equipping the platform with advanced stealth and concealment systems. The result was a scout suit that could move overland while remaining hidden, a first for Republic infantry.</p><p>Field testing with the VIII Hastati Sentinels validated the concept during a counterinsurgency operation on Shipka, where an Angerona squad stalked and eliminated two squads of Capellan-backed Ying Long suits after watching a friendly Purifier squad fall in ambush. The suit's performance accelerated adoption across Republic line units, including Stone's Lament and the Liberators. A dedicated recon configuration followed in 3085, and the Quartermaster's office soon began accepting broader requisitions.</p>
</history>

